The paper discusses a method for maintaining the accuracy of supervised learning models in the presence of evolving data streams, which is a common problem in machine learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses sampling schemes and algorithms for dynamic streaming data, which are relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Database (cs.DB) sub-categories. The paper's focus on adapting to recent changes in the data and maintaining robustness suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
